    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1174"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1174">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.20 Missions/9–1845</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">French Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Syrian Government has requested an American Military Mission to assist it in
                    the organization and training of the Syrian defense and security forces,
                    consisting largely of the Syrian troops recently transferred to Syrian control
                    by the French authorities.</p>
                <p>The Syrian Government’s request is now being considered by this Government, which
                    would be glad to receive an expression of the views of the French Government in
                    this connection.</p>
                <p>A similar communication is being transmitted to the British Embassy.<note n="26"
                        xml:id="d1174fn26">September 19, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                        mutandis</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-19">September 19,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
